cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.HC, cs.SI, cs.CY 

The paper proposes a computer vision-based framework for crowd management in the scared cities of Makkah Al Mukarramah and Madina Al Munawarah during Hajj. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the challenges of crowd management, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia), cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper mentions the need for customization of existing approaches, which could be related to cs.CY (Computers and Society).
